[[File:Red spiders' eggs detail.png|left|150px]]
'''Red spiders' eggs''' are a [[Herblore]] ingredient that [[members]] can use to make one of three different potions. Those with level 22 Herblore can combine them with a [[harralander potion (unf)]] (made by adding [[harralander]] to a [[vial of water]]) to make a [[restore potion]] and gain 62.5 [[experience]] points. Those with level 63 Herblore can combine the eggs with a [[snapdragon potion (unf)]] (made by adding [[snapdragon]] to a vial of water) to make a [[Super restore|super restore potion]] and gain 142.5 experience. Those with level 73 herblore can combine the eggs with [[coconut milk]] and a [[cactus spine]] to make [[weapon poison(+)]] and gain 165 experience.

All players can give red spiders' eggs along with a [[limpwurt root]] and 5 [[coins]] to the [[apothecary]] in [[Varrock]], and he will give them a 4-dose [[strength potion]] in return.

==Obtaining red spiders' eggs==
Red spiders' eggs [[Spawning|spawn]] in a number of places, especially areas where [[deadly red spider]]s can be found. Spawn points include:
*The [[Varrock Sewers]] - 2 egg spawns (respawns every 60 seconds, requires a knife to slash the web). One of only two F2P spawn locations, the other is Karamja Volcano.
*The [[Edgeville Dungeon]] - 6 egg spawns (members only, as the wilderness section of the Edgeville Dungeon is members only - and contains all 6 egg spawns)
**By using the [[looting bag]], a player can quickly collect the red spiders' eggs with ease as the eggs are located in the [[Wilderness]]. Beware of [[player killer]]s.
*The [[Karamja Volcano]] - 1 egg spawn (every 60 seconds). One of only two F2P spawn locations, the other is Varrock Sewers.
*Along the path to [[Tirannwn]] from the main gate ([[members]] only, requires start of the [[Regicide]] [[quest]] and completion of its prerequisite quests) - 6 egg spawns
*The [[Forthos Dungeon]] - 11 egg spawns in Spider Den (every 50 seconds). Furthermore, the [[temple spider]]s there commonly drop noted eggs.
*[[Creature Creation]] - Players who have completed the [[Tower of Life]] quest may offer 1 red spiders' egg and 1 [[raw sardine]] at the proper [[Symbol of life]] to summon a level 42 [[Spidine]] which drops 3-6 red spiders' eggs when killed.
*[[Venenatis]] will uncommonly drop 500 noted eggs.
*[[Sarachnis]] will commonly drop a [[Giant egg sac]], which can be opened for 100 eggs.

